works.description: The Destination: Earlier, we saw the At.mosphere, the world’s highest restaurant and last week, Ritz-Carlton has opened what is being said to be the world’s highest hotel located on floors 102 to 118 in the 1,588-foot International Commerce Centre in Hong Kong. Sitting 490 meters above Victoria Harbour in the Kohn Pedersen Fox Associates-designed building, the Ritz-Carlton hotel offers its guests a breathtaking 360-degree view of the entire city and surrounding islands. The new property is the company’s 16th hotel in Asia.
